We are currently consulting on the frequency and scope of the Traveller Caravan Count data collection. The consultation is open until 24 December 2025. For more information and to share your views, please go to Traveller caravan count statistics - GOV.UK



3. Count of Traveller Caravans


Local authorities carried out the July 2025 count on or around 17 July 2025. Aggregated totals by site type are presented in Table 1 below, and comparative figures from the previous count are presented in Table 2. At the time of the July 2025 count, the total number of traveller caravans in England was 28,589. Of these 6,267 (22%) were on socially rented sites; 17,858 (62%) were on privately funded sites; 3,880 (14%) were unauthorised developments on land owned by travellers; and 584 (2%) were unauthorised encampments on land not owned by travellers. This information is also illustrated in Figure 1 below and in accompanying Live Table 1. The next count of new affordable residential pitches would typically take place as part of the July 2026 count of traveller caravans. However, publication of this data is subject to the outcome of the (November/December 2025) consultation on the Traveller Caravan Count, which is considering, among other things, whether this information should be collected as part of a different data collection as well as the frequency of the count. It should be noted that the reported increase in unauthorised developments is due in part to improved reporting in this category; data providers are encouraged to report the excess caravans on sites with planning permission as unauthorised developments where the planning permission has been breached or exceeded.



