6. New Affordable Residential Pitches


As part of the July count, local authorities are required to submit data on the number of new affordable rental pitches constructed since the previous year’s count. The number of new affordable residential pitches in each local authority area in England has been collected since July 2011 (whilst the July 2020 count was cancelled, information on new affordable residential pitches was still collected from local authorities). This has previously been reported to allow such pitches to be included in the calculation of the New Homes Bonus for individual local authorities. Table 3 below shows that, local authorities reported no new affordable residential pitches on socially rented or privately funded sites created between July 2024 and July 2025. Further details are provided in accompanying Live Table 5.

The next count of new affordable residential pitches would typically take place as part of the July 2026 count of traveller caravans. However, publication of this data is subject to the outcome of the (November/December 2025) consultation on the Traveller Caravan Count, which is considering, among other things, whether this information should be collected as part of a different data collection as well as the frequency of the count.



